ARCTIC MONKEYS - S.I.N.G.L.E.S. (Deluxe Edition) (2014

S.I.N.G.L.E.S. is a compilation album featuring every single (commercial and promotional) by Arctic Monkeys. Arctic Monkeys are an English indie rock band formed in 2002 in High Green, a suburb of Sheffield. The band consists of Alex Turner (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Jamie Cook (lead guitar, backing vocals in the early days), Nick O'Malley (bass, backing vocals), and Matt Helders (drums, backing vocals). Former band member Andy Nicholson (bass guitar, backing vocals) left the band in 2006 shortly after its debut album was released
